# Integration test: IIcx Boot
# Boots IIcx (no SCSI/floppy attached) to the "insert disk" floppy
# icon screen and verifies the display matches the reference image.
#
# Same cycle budget as the SE/30 boot test — both share the Universal
# ROM and reach SCSI_WAIT_BSY in roughly the same number of instructions.

scheduler.run 335000000

assert ${machine.id == "iicx"} "machine.id != iicx"
assert ${screen.width == 640} "screen.width != 640 (NuBus card not seated?)"
assert ${screen.height == 480} "screen.height != 480"

# Verify the screen matches the floppy icon reference image
# (gray desktop + cursor in top-left + insert-disk icon centered).
screen.match floppy.png

quit
